Show HN: Phone Booth Privacy – Call Spam and Scam Protection for Android
text:
Hi HN,

I have been working on this app for a while now and released it today it as Early Access to get feedback. Call spam is one of the major problems that I face everyday and that I want to solve for myself. Just to give a background, I’m a very private person, using barely any social media (usually 1-to-1 messaging apps or no-login lurker), and hate ads, dark patterns and dumbing down stuff for users by hiding away information.

As such, I've been developing this app while ensuring it passes my own bar for my personal use. It is bare-bones as of now, and provides basic call management and block list. I’m working to add more stuff to it, including advanced blocking features and caller ID. This is a product-of-one, and will always remain so.

Please download it from Google Play Store for Android and let me know your feedback. There is no sign-up required, and even though the Data Sharing section on Play Store page and Privacy Policy mentions about data collection (like Call Log), the backend hasn’t been integrated in this version of the app, so, it is completely offline / standalone.

https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.hyprgeek.p...

Thanks,

Ask HN: Facebook disabled account, how to make sure personal data gets deleted?
text:
Long story short: Facebook has decided to disable my account due to "severe violations of Facebook Community Standards". I have not logged into my account for a half a year and was not active user before then. Recovering account is out of the question, as appeal must be sent 30 days after account was disabled, but nobody actually bothered to inform me about it. No matter, getting rid of Facebook is a win in my book.

Now for main question: How do I make sure that all of my personal data gets wiped from Facebook servers? Incidentally the data download fails due to some "technical errors" and I cannot check what personal data is left on Facebook.
